column5: Wow! Thx John! Lots of water, I think that's a good sign.
Hope you didn't drive over any walleyes on the road and smash them,could have been a few 30 inch'ers there.
30 inchers are swimming upstream, heading for rapids. Will soon be honeymooning.
Maybe go back later and troll for pike.
This water goes into Wabigoon river and then Clay Lake which will rise 4-6 ft most years.
just tie some long leaders to your bumper and drive back and forth !
Pretty sure tgey are tgere now.just waiting for water temp to rise
He be the first one ever to catch a northern trolling with a 2022 f150 truck
